The England international took his position at Old Trafford, next to representative Aidy Ward, for the quarter-final tie.

United, who look unlikely to keep Radamel Falcao when his loan spell expires at the end of the season, will look to bolster their forward line this summer.

Berahino has impressed this season, scoring 18 goals for the Baggies - as well as three for England Under 21s.

Liverpool and Tottenham have both shown an interest in Berahino this season.

